#Day 2: Git Basics - Local Setup and Remote Connection

##What I Did:
Installed and configured Git on my local machine.

Explored fundamental Git commands like git init, git add, and git commit.

Created a local project and made my first commit to the repository's history.

Learned how to connect a local repository to a remote GitHub repository.

Successfully pushed my project to GitHub for the first time.

The main takeaway was understanding the core workflow of saving my work locally and synchronizing it with my online GitHub repository.
